1.we will have to install PyInputPlus seperately using pip.>>pip install PyInputPlus
2.because PyInputPlus is not included in the default packages in python.
3.inputInt() is for taking integer inputs where as inputFloat() is for taking floating inputs.
4.>>import pyinputplus as pyip
    >>pyip.inputNum('Enter num:',min=0,max=99)
6.Not allowed to enter one more time
7.default value is taken when blank is entered 3 times
